    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"moving into a new chapter\" usually means living through it, right? like, continuing the story? but when i think about surrendering to the universe, it doesn't feel like a new chapter in this life. it feels like the end of the book. it feels like leaving this world behind entirely. is that a bad thing? am i being \"spiritual\" if i feel like the only way to truly find peace is to finally cross over?",
